category: RELIGIOUS RANKS & TITLES
category comment: 

clue: In Buddhism, an arhat is one who has attained this through ascetic practices & meditation

response: enlightenment (nirvana)

clue: Also called a hazan, it's the person who leads a synagogue congregation in song

response: a cantor

clue: The Quorum of Twelve these are a governing body in the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints

response: Apostles

clue: Familiar from Monty Python sketches, this word for an Anglican or Episcopal priest is from the Latin for "substitute"

response: vicar

clue: Dervishes that engage in ecstatic whirling & dancing are members of this mystical practice of Islam

response: Sufi

